22/12/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police arrested an armed man who held an employee of a tax office in the western town of Vonitsa hostage for over two hours Tuesday (December 21st).
Before the arrest, the man, 47, opened fire;
a police officer he hit suffered a minor wound.
Officials say the gunman, who appeared to have a gripe with tax authorities, ordered all employees of the office to leave the building but one.
She was not harmed in the incident.
(AP, AFP, ANA-MPA - 21/12/10)
